Some progress on debugging. I see two issues here:

An iterator `TSNode:_rawquery()` would enumerate "captures" `(capture_id: integer, node: TSNode, match: TSMatch)`

- First, **`match` is nil** from the second capture. Therefore, the information whether a predicate has been filtered out this match is *lost* for this capture. 
  - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/v0.9.5/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua#L649-L658
  - https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/v0.9.5/src/nvim/lua/treesitter.c#L1334
  - This confirms that #23664 (reports wrong information from the second capture within a match) is also caused by the same issue.

- Second, the same instance of `match` Lua table is returned across different matches. This is C implementation issue -- we should be returning a copy (Cf. #17099 tries to create a new table, so could be a relevant fix). This wouldn't be a big problem unless the mutating table `match` is stored somewhere other than the predicates.
  - See the highlighted line below in the tracing result.
 
This bug has existed since the first implementation 440695c29696f261337227e5c419aa1cf313c2dd of treesitter. My question is: Is the behavior of `query_next_capture` [returning only 2 values: `[index, node]`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/v0.9.5/src/nvim/lua/treesitter.c#L1334), `match` being `nil` intended? /cc @bfredl If not, I can fix this to always return the correct, non-nil `match` table.


### Tracing Result

Traces in the chronological order; important lines are highlighted.

For the first match:

```diff
 -- [iter_captures:raw_iter] {{ 
+	match = table: 0x0101fb8d70 { <userdata<node field_identifier> 1>, pattern = 1 }
 	capture_id = 1, captured_node = <userdata<node field_identifier> 1> range={ 0, 3, 0, 8 }
 -- }}
 -- predicate returned TRUE
 -- match is not nil, predicates have been applied.
 capture_id=1 @_field   : node = Query, metadata = {}
 
 -- [iter_captures:raw_iter] {{ 
-	match =  nil
 	capture_id = 2, captured_node = <userdata<node interpreted_string_literal> 1> range={ 0, 9, 0, 29 }
 -- }}
--- 汾 match == nil, so predicates are not applied.
capture_id=2 @sql      : node = "INTERPRETED STRING", metadata = {}
```

For the second match:
```diff
 -- [iter_captures:raw_iter] {{ 
+	match = table: 0x0101fb8d70 { <userdata<node field_identifier> 1>, active = true, pattern = 1 }
 	capture_id = 1, captured_node = <userdata<node field_identifier> 1> range={ 1, 3, 1, 11 }
 -- }}
+-- predicate returned FALSE, excluding this match
 --------------- tail call: try next match -----------------
 
 -- [iter_captures:raw_iter] {{ 
-	match =  nil
 	capture_id = 2, captured_node = <userdata<node raw_string_literal> 1> range={ 1, 12, 1, 24 
 }
 -- }}
--- 汾 match == nil, so predicates are not applied.
 capture_id=2 @sql      : node = `RAW STRING`, metadata = {}
```

(iterator terminates)

```
-- [iter_captures:raw_iter] {{ 
	match =  nil
	capture_id = nil, captured_node = nil 
-- }}
```
